{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17636759","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17636759"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T18:33:08+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T18:33:08+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17603"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17603","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17603"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.09,0.13,0,0.78]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10317"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71551"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10317","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10317"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17603"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57040"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"10017"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24126"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24131"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24144"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71551","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/71551"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe pancreas secretes both digestive enzymes and alkaline fluid in response to the presence of food in the small intestine. This process is regulated by gastrointestinal hormones. Cholecystokinin is one such hormone and acts on pancreatic secretion.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes its primary action on pancreatic secretion?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Increases pancreatic blood flow only","Inhibits both enzyme and bicarbonate secretion","Increases bicarbonate secretion from duct cells","Stimulates water secretion from duct cells","Stimulates enzyme secretion from acinar cells"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe primary action of cholecystokinin is to \u003Cstrong\u003Estimulate enzyme secretion from pancreatic acinar cells\u003C/strong\u003E. When food enters the duodenum, cholecystokinin is released from enteroendocrine cells and acts directly on acinar cells to trigger the release of digestive enzymes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreases bicarbonate secretion from duct cells\u003C/strong\u003E - This is the primary action of secretin, not cholecystokinin\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInhibits both enzyme and bicarbonate secretion\u003C/strong\u003E - Cholecystokinin stimulates rather than inhibits secretion\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStimulates water secretion from duct cells\u003C/strong\u003E - Water secretion follows bicarbonate secretion, which is controlled by secretin\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreases pancreatic blood flow only\u003C/strong\u003E - While blood flow may increase, the primary action is enzyme secretion\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECholecystokinin works in concert with secretin, which stimulates bicarbonate-rich fluid secretion, to produce appropriate pancreatic secretions for digestion.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Cholecystokinin stimulates pancreatic enzyme secretion via direct action on pancreatic acinar cells.","Secretin stimulates bicarbonate-rich fluid secretion from pancreatic duct cells.","Both cholecystokinin and secretin are released from duodenal enteroendocrine cells in response to food."],"references":["Tortora GJ, Derrickson BH, Burkett B, Peoples G, Dye D, Cooke J, et al. Principles of Anatomy and Physiology, 2nd Asia-Pacific Edition: John Wiley \u0026 Sons, Limited; 2019","Hall J. Guyton and Hall Textbook of Medical Physiology. 14th ed. Elsevier Health Sciences; 2021. https://clinicalkeymeded.elsevier.com/reader/books/9780323597128"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57040"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17603"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57040","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/57040"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-19T09:58:13+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-19T09:58:50+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10317"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71551"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4928","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4928"},"attr